
<!-- I set the base application's theme to this theme, stockpile_Theme. Android will automatically
inherit a theme depending on the device's version (i.e. if I run v20, then theme in values is used.
If I run v12,, then theme in v11 is used). To ensure a cohesive experience, I inherit a base
theme from android depending on what was most popular during this version's cycle.

Anyway, essentially this theme defines what styles to use for each widget (and if not
defined, then it uses whatever the parent is using). So some resources are found in
stockTheme_Styles.xml -->

<resources>
    
    <style name="stockpile_Theme" parent="android:Theme.Holo.Light.DarkActionBar">
        <!-- Remove the title bar -->
	    <item name="android:windowActionBar">false</item>
    	<item name="android:windowNoTitle">true</item>
    	
		<item name="android:windowBackground">@drawable/appbg</item>
    	
    	<item name="android:textViewStyle">@style/textstyle</item>
    	<item name="android:buttonStyle">@style/buttonstyle</item>
	    
	    
    </style>
    
</resources>